{
  "texts": [
    "Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) (Yu et al., 2019) networks are a variation of RNNs that address issues of gradient vanishing and exploding by introducing mechanisms such as memory cells, input gates, forget gates, and output gates.",
    "Wan et al. (2020) proposed a short text clustering model ST-CNN.",
    "BiLSTM+CNN was used to mine the context information of short texts and obtain deep semantic text feature vectors.",
    "The ELMO model is essentially a two-layer bidirectional LSTM language model (Peters et al., 2018).",
    "The forward language model learns the semantic information of a word within its following context, and similarly, the backward language model learns the semantic information of the word within its preceding context."
  ]
}